	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have defended Verant for 10 months now, but this is absolute and utter bull****. I bought into your nonsense about BALANCE hook, line and sinker for all this time. What I've found is that players don't give one DAMN about balance, only Verant. That's fine, it's your game. But you are unbalancing Clerics and the entire nature of the game with your recent changes.<BR>
<BR>
When I began playing, VI was very clear with class descriptions... Clerics are THE healer class. Paladins are closely in cahoots with Clerics, but obviously not as much of a healer. Now, you have doubly penalized Clerics and ruined their very existence. Druids and Shamans get increased healing powers, Clerics get theirs reduced. Paladins, as usual, get absolutely NOTHING as far as healing changes, yet VI themselves insist that the Paladin is the closest relative of the Cleric.<BR>
<BR>
Druids are now the least-respected class in Norrath, as they have EVERYTHING except armor, but can kite their way to 60 and don't really need it. Druids are laughable as the obvious choice for the lazy and less-skilled player. Add their teleporting costs and your BALANCE issue has created a class that is hated by all others.<BR>
<BR>
Shamans were well-known as buff-machines, and VI has many times stated that their secondary role was as a tank. Now, of course, they become better healers too! Add all this crap with the fact that classes are being given Undead Invis powers, etc. What a joke! Pallys, Clerics, and Necros are becoming more useless to others every day. But, OH, VI claims the game's purpose is to promote grouping! Well, congrats, as my Pally (and he's a damn good one) takes hours to build his own group. Thankfully, I have friends who don't care that I have limited skills in Velious, considering it's vast lack of Undead foes. Thanks a hell of a bunch for wasting my money, Verant.<BR>
<BR>
To finalize this rant, I want you to know that I am very close to suggesting to all of my player friends the solution of finding a different game to waste our hours on. VI takes very few suggestions, go ahead and play God, but not with my money much longer! If this unbalanced blending of powers doesn't stop soon, I see no reason to continue playing this game. Classes were specific in powers just 10 months ago, now they are not. Yet you arbitrarily decide which classes get benefits, completely unfair! The nerfs, the ridiculous drop-times and camps, the stupid massive HPs on greenies in Velious, it's all combined to make players die more, play longer, and thus more money for Verant. The fun is going away quickly, and so will your profits unless you take some valid suggestions from your cash-cows... US.<BR>
<BR>
I put 10 months into my character and I'm not about to waste 10 more to create another one. I certainly have no desire to ever create a cleric now, although my friends are ready to quit after wasting a year making theirs. Either do something right for once, or Ultima has at least 30 new players. you aren't stealing another 10 months of my free-time without a damn good reason.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
